title: DB2: Databases Connections and Query Latency
agents: aix, linux
catalog: app/db2
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the number of connections to a DB2 database.

 It also outputs the connection latency (no limits configurable).

 You can configure limits for the number of connections.

 This check needs the mk_db2 plugin installed in the agent.

item:
 The DB2 instance name followed by a : and the database name, e.g. db2ilog1:REST1

discovery:
 One service is created for each database.
